Description:
Indoor/Outdoor Sanctuary with Incredible Views
The sky's the limit to the relaxed private enjoyment, contemporary style and stunning uninterrupted views presented by this compelling penthouse-level warehouse residence. Rare north and west orientation, 2 interconnected decks and amazing 5th floor outlooks to the CBD and northern horizon highlight this unique multi-level retreat blending innovative design, excellent features and flowing indoor/outdoor spaces. Secure and secluded offering 2-car basement parking, video intercom, lift access, 2/3 beautiful big robed bedrooms (main with ensuite plus direct access to tranquil BBQ deck with water feature and garden; 2nd with extra deep storage), versatile mezzanine study, upper level lounge opening to west deck, large open-plan living and dining zone with Smeg equipped kitchen and storage, stylish bathroom, bulkhead air-conditioning, zoned ducted heating, tinted/UV treated windows, Verosol blinds, eco-friendly waxed double-thick floorboards, quality carpets, high ceilings and deck lighting. Superbly positioned near shopping, cafes, bars, galleries, trams, parks and the city.
Insights: 24/125 Oxford Street, Collingwood VIC 3066 was last sold in 2017 and 18 other 3 bedroom unit in Collingwood have recently been sold.

Description:
Beautifully Balanced Victorian
The perfect blend of old and new. Character-filled & exceptionally renovated with modern comforts this freestanding Victorian is one of the most beautiful cottages in Collingwood, offering a fabulous low maintenance lifestyle just moments from the city in quiet neighbourly position. Offering 2 double bedrooms both with built in robes, wonderfully bright and spacious open plan living and dining opening to fantastic courtyard with timber decking, stylish stainless steel kitchen with DW & gas cooktop, updated central bathroom with claw-foot bath and separate laundry. Substantial property size offers plenty of space for those looking to expand the family home (STCA). Features include polished boards, period detail, reverse cycle heating & cooling plus rear lane access all set in a row of classic Victorian terraces just a short stroll to Gertrude & Smith Street, Victoria Streets cafes, restaurants, shopping and transport plus East Melbourne Parks/Gardens and MCG close by.
Insights: 43 Campbell Street, Collingwood VIC 3066 was last sold in 2017 and 29 other 2 bedroom house in Collingwood have recently been sold.

Description:
Smart inner city solution
A position that offers exceptional access Smith Street enhances this two bedroom apartment's sleek city style and large terrace, highlighting its tremendous appeal as a lifestyle, investment or inner urban base asset. Tucked away in modern “Marque”, a cleverly designed layout hosts two double bedrooms with built in robes, a sophisticated stone topped bathroom and smart and spacious living/dining domain with seamless stainless steel appointed kitchen. Floor to ceiling glass and sliding doors link this zone to a beautifully broad undercover terrace whose leafy views over landscaped communal gardens create a tranquil backdrop for living and entertaining. Reverse cycle heating/cooling, intercom security, residents' rooftop terrace and a lift accessed basement carspace confirm further comfort just steps from trams, shops, cafes, restaurants and nightlife.
Sam Abboud : 0401 434 329

Description:
Melbourne meets Manhattan
Situated in Collingwood's iconic Foy & Gibson warehouse precinct, this 'New York on Oxford' apartment invokes a New York state of mind with its vast open spaces, bold industrial cues and towering ceilings throughout. Bathed in natural light, the home's bespoke interior showcases 3 bedrooms (2 extra-large) all with robes, mezzanine study, deluxe ensuite and main bathroom. Add to this an incredibly spacious open-design living/dining area enhanced by a quality kitchen with breakfast bar and Bosch dishwasher, plus heating and cooling, exposed girders and hardwood floors, feature doors, alarm, lift to secure foyer, two car spaces and storage cage. Quality, class and inner-city convenience, it's a short stroll to Smith Street trams, cafes and restaurants, shops and supermarkets. Absolutely amazing!

“North Facing Victorian with so much Potential”
Positioned to take full advantage of the amazing lifestyle attributes of urban Collingwood, this double fronted period home is ripe for an update.

Wonderful entry point, family size living.

NEW YORK STYLE LOFT

This smartly refurbished semi-detached residence entered via a private courtyard offers a classic floor plan comprising 3 double bedrooms from an arched hallway, spacious living room with OFP, neat functional kitchen open to a conservatory-style dining zone, plus bathroom/laundry with timber cabinetry and a northerly courtyard with pedestrian ROW access. Close to Smith St cafes, and Queens Parade shops and transport, this appealing home features loft storage, polished timber floors, new carpets and ducted heating.

Description:
Space and style: a conversion of rare refinement
Soaring spaces, a versatile floor plan and bespoke fittings are the hallmarks of this former tool factory, stunningly converted by renowned architect Robert Busselmann. Combining original industrial detail with warm timber finishes, and featuring an award-winning kitchen and bathroom designed by Patricia LaTorre Interiors, this exceptional residence offers a dramatic living/dining room with beam and truss ceiling, opening through timber multifolds to a wide al fresco entertaining terrace with northerly views; expansive entrance gallery and second living zone; state-of-the-art kitchen with premium fittings; 3 large double bedrooms (striking ensuite to main); Italian-tiled main bathroom with walk-in shower, powder room, laundry and 2-car garage. Bordering Smith Street bars and cafes, this remarkable CBD-fringe home features polished eucalypt and concrete floors, generous custom storage, LUMP light-fittings, hydronic heating, air conditioning, security and cabling.
Insights: 11 Little Wellington Street, Collingwood VIC 3066 was last sold in 2017 and 24 other 3 bedroom house in Collingwood have recently been sold.

Description:
Swipe right and stroll to Smith St!
Location doesn't get much hipper than the heart of Collingwood's Foy and Gibson heritage precinct and this brilliant one-bedroom studio apartment places you just a lazy stroll from the cafes, bars and restaurants of Smith St and Gertrude St to offer the ideal inner city lifestyle. Designed by award-winning architects Elenberg Fraser, Oxley Apartments were a project of prominent Melbourne Property developers Urban Inc., custom-built to offer occupants a secure urban sanctuary to call home.
Beyond the apartment the lush exterior landscape provides plenty of options for entertaining, whether beside the rooftop garden terrace or swimming in the stunning pool overlooking Collingwood's decommissioned industrial factories. Inside, a convenient open-plan layout incorporates the efficient contemporary kitchen equipped with quality stainless steel appliances, while an enclosed balcony adds further versatility with scope for a light-filled sitting room or possible home office/study. Accommodation includes built-in robes, while the sleek fully-tiled bathroom with roomy shower and space saving European laundry is draped in designer style.
Less than 4km from the CBD, Oxley Apartments residents enjoy the ideal balance of work and play, while property features include reverse-cycle air-conditioning, double glazed windows, secure video intercom entry and a handy storage cage.
Anthony Cimino : 0400 500 903

Description:
Sensational Starter or Blue-Chip Investment
One of only twelve in a secure refurbished block, this second-floor corner abode is perfectly positioned to take advantage of every lifestyle advantage Collingwood has to offer. Bathed in natural light, the apartment's pristine interior comprises two double bedrooms (both with robes), stylish bathroom and separate WC, open lounge/dining area with city skyline views. Add to this an updated kitchen with stainless steel cooking appliances and built-in breakfast bar, internal laundry facilities, intercom/secure entry foyer, plus lock-up garage via gated driveway. Easey access to Smith Street cafes and trams, renowned restaurants and shopping precincts, as well as Johnston Street buses and Victoria Park Station.

Description:
Contemporary Warehouse with Incredible Views
Within Melbourne's historic 'Foy & Gibson' warehouses, this stunning two bedroom conversion blends original character features with contemporary interiors to create luxury inner-city living.
Lofty ceilings with magnificent exposed beams, original Baltic floors and vast living spaces are key design elements of this stylish warehouse conversion.
Situated on the 5th floor with lift access, the entry foyer leads into an open plan living and dining area showcasing 3 large sash windows which fill the apartment with natural light and offer stunning easterly views.
The well-appointed kitchen has vast storage, stone bench tops and modern appliances.
The property has two bedrooms, both with large built-in robes and ceiling fans and a large central bathroom including a full-sized bath and European laundry.
Additional features include a remote-controlled secure undercover car space, elevator access from car park to the apartment and a secure intercom.
Located in the heart of Collingwood there are endless options for casual or fine dining, art galleries and all within walking distance to sport, shopping and the CBD.
Insights: 504/103 Oxford Street, Collingwood VIC 3066 was last sold in 2017 and 83 other 2 bedroom unit in Collingwood have recently been sold.

Description:
Sensational new concept for inner-urban living
A sophisticated, contemporary design fused into a raw industrial setting, this brand new, spacious first-floor apartment is part of an exciting and unique New York loft-inspired vision of inner city living.
Accessed via lift from the secure video entry foyer, the open living/meals zone features a sleek marble-topped kitchen with stainless steel Ilve appliances, mirrored splashback and soft-close cabinetry, looking across a large covered balcony to a captivating urban view directly up Oxford Street.
Contrasting distressed concrete ceilings and exposed brick with engineered timber floors and modern surfaces, appreciate two robed double bedrooms (main with marble ensuite and study nook), a stylish central bathroom, split system heating and cooling, basement car stacker parking and a storage cage.
Grab an all-day breakfast at the popular Proud Mary cafe, or explore Smith Street for a great selection of eateries, boutique shopping, nightlife, supermarket and tram into the CBD. Walk to Fitzroy Gardens and the city.
* Brand new 2 bedroom, 2 bathroom apartment
* Open-plan living/meals, covered balcony with striking view
* Marble kitchen with stainless steel Ilve appliances
* Soft-close cabinetry and integrated dishwasher
* Secure basement car stacker space plus storage cage
* Surrounded by cafes, restaurants and boutique shopping
* Take the tram or walk to the CBD and Fitzroy Gardens
Also visit the stand alone website at: www.102-24-28stanleystcollingwood.com
Terms: 10% deposit, balance 30 days

Description:
Contemporary class and spectacular views
Quality and style over two levels in the heart of Collingwood's iconic Foy & Gibson precinct, this top-floor Gibsonia townhouse offers penthouse-size proportions, a long list of features and breathtaking views all the way to the Dandenong Ranges. Light-filled interior boasts 2 large bedrooms (master with WIR and enormous private terrace), study alcove and 2 deluxe bathrooms, well-appointed kitchen and vast open-plan living/dining area leading out to a full-width balcony to relax/entertain and enjoy the 180° panorama. Add to this split-system heating and cooling, stone benchtops, under-stair storage, full-size laundry, plus intercom, lift access to secure entry foyer, parking space and large walk-in storage cage. City-fringe living at its best; Smith Street cafes and restaurants, shops and supermarkets, city-bound trams are all within easy reach.

Description:
Heritage glory in Yorkshire Brewery
Entry via Waterloo Road. Sure to astound the most astute of buyers with its treasured heritage detail blending seamlessly with considered luxury, this town residence is unforgettable living in a prized inner city pocket. Part of the esteemed Yorkshire Brewery complex, this dual level dwelling makes an instant impact with dark timber floors, double brick walls, and 4.2 metre exposed concrete ceilings through spacious lounge and dining. A marble kitchen is complete with Miele appliances including dual ovens and an integrated dishwasher, meanwhile both upstairs bedrooms are a tremendous size including the master retreat which showcases an exquisite ensuite. The central bathroom is a sea of gorgeous marble while further enjoying a freestanding bath with rain shower. Other additions include a powder room, European laundry, reverse cycle cooling, video intercom, two car spaces, and access to a gym, library, dining room and ninth floor BBQ terrace. Near lively Smith Street, Collingwood College and Collingwood Station.
Insights: 1 Brewery Lane, Collingwood VIC 3066 was last sold in 2017 and 29 other 2 bedroom house in Collingwood have recently been sold.

Description:
Spacious living with city views
Welcome to Islington Street, Collingwood; once the home of the James Hood & Co Malt House, now an opportunity for spacious inner city living in one of the most stylish and sought-after suburbs in Melbourne.
Flexible living spaces include a large ground-floor 3rd bedroom/lounge or home office, upstairs master bedroom with walk-in-robe and en-suite bathroom, spacious 2nd bedroom and retreat. Plus spacious top-floor open-plan living/dining area and study nook, modern kitchen with stainless steel Blanco appliances and a sliding door to the balcony makes this an ideal home for entertaining and enjoying the city views.
Add to this, ducted heating and cooling, security system, new carpets and solid timber floors, ample storage cupboards, laundry and private double garage (remote-controlled) with internal entry.
Positioned within 5 minutes walk to North Richmond Station and even less to Victoria Parade trams, this super-sized townhouse is the perfect choice for those seeking quality, style and convenience.

Description:
Designer style over 2 spacious levels

Bathed in natural light, the home's vogue interior showcases 2 bedrooms (extra-large master) both with BIRs, deluxe bathroom and powder room (second WC), plus Smeg-equipped kitchen with stone benchtops and soft-close drawers complementing the vast and versatile open-plan living/dining areas. Description:
Spacious In and Out
A contemporary new residential neighbourhood, formally the Yorkshire Brewery right in the heart of Collingwood, located in close proximity to East Melbourne, Fitzroy and the CBD, transport, parklands, sporting precincts and an abundance of awesome cafes, bars and restaurants. This as new apartment comprises one bedroom (BIR's), stylish tiled bathroom with laundry facilities, open plan kitchen, meals and living zone which leads out on to a large terrace balcony perfect for relaxing or entertaining friends and family. Other features include SS appliances, timber flooring, split system heating/cooling and secure car park. A safe and well maintained complex with on-site building manager and security surveillance, residents also enjoy the use of the rooftop entertaining lounge area with BBQ facilities, gym, private library, private kitchen and dining room to host your own dinner party and even a furnished apartment for the use of family short stays at a reasonable cost. Nelson Alexander Pty Ltd
